From: Refracta user
Date: 2026-07-05
Subject: [PATCH] refractasnapshot: default "seed /etc/skel + UEFI" snapshot mode

Incorporates the standalone /etc/skel seeding step directly into refractasnapshot
(both CLI and GUI), the same way btrfs-disk-lib.sh was folded into
refractainstaller: a shared library is the single source of truth, sourced by
the snapshot tools and by the standalone seed script.

New shared library (created by this patch):

  usr/lib/refractasnapshot/skel-seed-lib.sh
    Defines WHAT gets seeded into /etc/skel (dotfiles + KDE/Plasma config +
    ~/.local/share app data + a bulk ~/.config sync with exclusions) and the
    copy logic. Sourcing only defines functions; refracta_seed_skel <home> does
    the work and never calls exit. Privilege model: writing /etc/skel needs root
    while reading the config needs the desktop user - _skel_as_root() runs direct
    when already root (refractasnapshot) or via sudo otherwise (standalone
    script), and refracta_skel_source_home() finds the desktop user's home even
    when the caller is root (SUDO_USER -> PKEXEC_UID -> uid-1000 fallback).

New default snapshot mode ("UEFI+Skel"):

  Both refractasnapshot and refractasnapshot-gui gain a new FIRST/default task,
  "Snapshot now: UEFI + seed /etc/skel from your desktop":
    - forces make_efi=yes (re-running check_grub so it still degrades safely if
      grub-efi-amd64/dosfstools are missing),
    - seeds /etc/skel from the desktop user's home BEFORE the filesystem is
      copied (so the seeded skel lands in the ISO),
    - runs in a "fast" path that skips the free-space report and the distro-name
      prompt, so the whole thing is one/two clicks (GUI) or ENTER (CLI).
  In the CLI it is menu item 0 and the default on an empty ENTER; in the GUI it
  is the pre-selected first row of the task list. The plain "Create a snapshot"
  task is unchanged (it just routes through the same shared body with seeding and
  fast-mode off). Tasks 2-6 are untouched.

Refactor:

  The task-1 body is factored into run_create_snapshot[_gui]() so the new default
  mode and the classic mode share one code path (flags: seed_skel, fast_mode).

Files:

  usr/bin/refractasnapshot-gui                     (GUI: default seed+UEFI task)
  usr/bin/refractasnapshot                         (CLI: default seed+UEFI task)
  usr/lib/refractasnapshot/skel-seed-lib.sh        (new shared library)

